long blow
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a long shearing stroke, with either shears or handpiece [usually to open the back fleece-wool.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
